cs.PL, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CC

This paper discusses language-integrated query techniques, which are commonly used in programming languages and databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the use of effects in Links, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of queries in databases, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the equivalence of two different approaches, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of a Links compiler, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
